The paper deals with understanding the reasoning behind the classification of speech utterances by deep neural networks. This involves training a classifier using the speech command corpus and using activation maximization to generate examples of different classes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with speech processing. The paper also involves subjective analysis and crowd-sourced human evaluations, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
